sentences: Lynn Morris (born October 8, 1948) is an American bluegrass musician.
In 1974, she won the National Banjo Championship, the first female to do so.
Assembling her own group, the Lynn Morris Band, in 1988, she began recording for Rounder Records.
She won several further bluegrass awards in the 1990s.

In 1996 the Lynn Morris Band performed in Scarborough, Ontario, Canada, as part of the Bluegrass Sundays winter concert series organized by the Northern Bluegrass Committee In 2005 the band entertained at the Gettysburg Bluegrass Festival.
